      • beginTime

        public final long beginTime()
        Returns the begin of the critical interaction with the system under test.
        Returns:
        When #startTimer() was called relative to the local clock (see Clock), in milliseconds.

      • endTime

        public final long endTime()
        Returns the end of the critical interaction with the system under test.
        Returns:
        When #stopTimer() was called relative to the local clock (see Clock), in milliseconds.

      • residenceTime

        public final double residenceTime()
                           throws RequestException
        Returns the duration of this request, i.e., the time (in milliseconds) elapsed between calling #startTimer() and #stopTimer().
        Returns:
        The residence time, i.e., the duration of this request in milliseconds.
        Throws:
        RequestException - When this request is not finished (i.e., both #startTimer() and #stopTimer() have not been called yet).

      • result

        public final RequestResult result()
        The result of this request. This value is RequestResult.NO_RESULT by default, but is changed via #done(RequestResult).
        Returns:
        The result of this request.

      • isDone

        public final boolean isDone()
        Check whether this request is already marked as done.
        Returns:
        Whether #startTimer() and #stopTimer() have been called, and whether a result has been set via #done(RequestResult).

      • type

        public java.lang.String type()
        Gets the name of this request type. This value is used to distinguish between different request types for the calculation of final request statistics. This value is set by the Request to which this RequestData object belongs.
        Returns:
        The short name of this request object.

      • thinkTime

        public int thinkTime()
        Returns the theoretical think time, in milliseconds, that the user sending this request should have waited before sending this request.
        Returns:
        The think time in milliseconds.
